    "department": "Legal",
    "description": "ABOUT SOLACE\n\nHealthcare in the U.S. is fundamentally broken. The system is so complex that 88% of U.S. adults do not have the health literacy necessary to navigate it without help. Solace cuts through the red tape of healthcare by pairing patients with expert advocates and giving them the tools to make better decisions—and get better outcomes.\n\nWe're a Series C startup, founded in 2022 and backed by Inspired Capital, Craft Ventures, Torch Capital, Menlo Ventures, Signalfire, and IVP. Our U.S. based team is lean, mission-driven, and growing quickly.\n\nSolace isn't a place to coast. We're here to redefine healthcare—and that demands urgency, precision, and heart. If you're looking to stretch yourself, sharpen your edge, and do the best work of your life alongside a team that cares deeply, you're in the right place. We’re intense, and we like it that way.\n\nRead more in our Bloomberg funding announcement here https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-02-10/vcs-give-solace-health-1-billion-valuation-for-patient-advocacy-tech?accessToken=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJzb3VyY2UiOiJTdWJzY3JpYmVyR2lmdGVkQXJ0aWNsZSIsImlhdCI6MTc3MDczMDg4MywiZXhwIjoxNzcxMzM1NjgzLCJhcnRpY2xlSWQiOiJUQThVUzhLR0NURzEwMCIsImJjb25uZWN0SWQiOiJBRDYxODI0MTc0ODM0MTk0QTRENUZFNzkwMzNGMDJGNSJ9.TE2pFUAOQAPMUXFlzoQ7zeJvctq7cSibbZqtIwhW-2U\u0026leadSource=uverify+wall.\n\n\nABOUT THE ROLE\n\nAs the Director of Compliance at Solace, you will build and own the systems that ensure we can deliver high-trust, high-impact patient advocacy at scale.\n\nSolace operates at the center of one of the most complex systems in the country, healthcare. We support patients navigating diagnoses, insurance battles, and care coordination across all 50 states, often at their most vulnerable moments. Compliance is not a back-office function here, it is core to how we earn and maintain trust with patients, advocates, and partners.\n\nYou will define how Solace operates within healthcare regulations while enabling the speed and ownership that make our advocates effective. You’ll take ambiguous, fragmented requirements across federal programs (including Medicare), state regulations, and privacy laws, and turn them into systems the company can actually run on.\n\nYou’re a builder who knows how to hold a high bar without becoming a bottleneck. You understand that the goal isn’t just to be compliant, it’s to build a system that works for patients.\n\nThis role will start as an individual contributor and evolve into building and leading a team. You will report directly to the CEO.\n\nWhat You’ll Do\n\nYou will own compliance end-to-end.\n\n - Build the Compliance Engine: Design and implement Solace’s compliance program across policies, controls, training, monitoring, and reporting built for a fast-moving, multi-state healthcare platform.\n\n - Translate Regulation into Execution: Turn complex requirements (HIPAA, Medicare, state-level rules, payer dynamics) into clear, actionable processes that operators and advocates can follow.\n\n - Own Marketplace Integrity: Define how Solace ensures its network of independent advocates operates safely, consistently, and in alignment with regulatory and ethical standards — without losing what makes them effective.\n\n - Embed Compliance into the Product: Partner with Product and Operations to ensure compliance is built into workflows like advocate matching, patient communication, documentation, and claims support.\n\n - Protect Patient Trust: Establish standards for privacy, data handling, and communication that reflect the reality of patients sharing highly sensitive information during critical moments.\n\n - Risk Identification \u0026 Control Design: Identify where things can break, across care coordination, insurance support, and patient interactions, and implement pragmatic controls that reduce risk without slowing down execution.\n\n - Audits \u0026 Investigations: Lead audits (internal and external), manage compliance reviews tied to Medicare and payer programs, and oversee investigations with speed and rigor.\n\n - Documentation That Reflects Reality: Create policies and procedures that match how Solace actually operates, and evolve them as the product and model change.\n\n - Monitoring \u0026 Reporting: Define KPIs and reporting that give leadership real visibility into compliance health, risks, and trends.\n\n - Vendor \u0026 Partner Oversight: Ensure third-party tools and partners meet Solace’s standards for privacy, security, and regulatory alignment.\n\n - Automation \u0026 Scale: Implement systems that reduce manual work, increase signal, and allow compliance to scale with the business.\n\nWhat You Bring to the Table\n\n - A bias toward action. You don’t just flag risk, you design and implement solutions.\n\n - Comfort operating in ambiguity, especially in environments where regulation and business models are evolving.\n\n - A builder’s mentality. You’ve built or scaled compliance programs in real-world, operationally complex settings.\n\n - Strong judgment. You know how to balance patient safety, regulatory integrity, and business velocity.\n\n - Ability to translate complex healthcare and payer regulations into clear, practical guidance.\n\n - Excellent communication and influence skills. You can partner across Product, Ops, and external stakeholders while holding a high bar.\n\n - Experience in healthcare, digital health, marketplaces, or similarly regulated environments strongly preferred.\n\n - Experience with HIPAA, Medicare (including Advantage plans), and multi-state regulatory environments.\n\n - Experience working with audits, investigations, and compliance program management.\n\n - 6–10+ years of experience in Compliance, Risk, Legal, or a related field, ideally in a high-growth environment.\n\nApplicants must be based in the United States.\n\nUp for the Challenge?\n\nWe look forward to meeting you.\n\nFraudulent Recruitment Advisory: Solace Health will NEVER request bank details or offer employment without an interview. All legitimate communications come from official solace.health emails only or ashbyhq.com http://ashbyhq.com. Report suspicious activity to recruiting@solace.health or advocate@solace.health.",
